FBIS4-13769 "drnes079_r_94005" FBIS-NES-94-079 Daily Report 24 Apr 1994 India Minister Criticizes Pakistan Travel Restrictions Minister Criticizes Pakistan Travel Restrictions BK2404090794 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 GMT 24 Apr 94 BK2404090794 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The minister of state for external affairs, Mr. R.L. Bhatia, has said that Pakistan's recent travel restrictions from and to India is another setback to bilateral relations. Talking to newsmen in Amritsar, he said Islamabad's intention seems to be to stop interaction between the people of the two countries. Mr. Bhatia reiterated India's stand on solving bilateral problems through dialogue.
